               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra Māryām "Miracles of Mary" (fols. 4ra-77vb)&#xD; I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 4ra-8ra)&#xD; I-2)
                     Introductive exhortation and hymns (fols. 8ra-10va)&#xD; I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd laki
                     wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki ... "I worship Thee ..." (fols. 10va-12rb)&#xD; I-4) Taʾammǝra
                     Māryām "Miracles of Mary": 90 miracles (fols. 12ra-77vb)&#xD; II) Taʾammǝra
                     Giyorgis "Miracles of George": 14 miracles (fols. 78ra-100rb)&#xD; &#xD;
                     Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>All miracles are numbered.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl ba-kǝlʾe Māryām walādita ʾamlāk ... "O my
                        Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, Godbearing ..." (<locus from="9rb" to="9va">9rb-9va</locus> l.16)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām Mariham ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos
                        kahāli ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty
                        ..." (<locus target="#9va">9va</locus> l.16-vb l.14)(cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma
                        bǝrhān ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of the
                        Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (<locus target="#9vb">9vb</locus>
                        l.14-10va)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-3 contains:</note>
                     <note>- Ṣalota za-yǝtbähal ʾǝmqǝdmä yanbǝbu täʾamriha la-ʾǝgzǝʾt kʷǝllǝnä ...
                        "Prayer recited before reading the Miracles of our Lady ..." (<locus from="11rb" to="12ra">11rb-12ra</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- Excerpt from the Gospel of John (Jn. 19:25-27) (<locus target="#12ra">12ra-</locus>rb).</note>
                  </msItem>
